# Development

## Prerequisites

- Ruby {{RUBY_VERSION}} â€” use [mise](https://mise.jdx.dev/) or [rbenv](https://github.com/rbenv/rbenv)
- SQLite3 (`apt install libsqlite3-dev` / `brew install sqlite`)
- [Bundler](https://bundler.io/) (`gem install bundler`)
- Optional: [overmind](https://github.com/DarthSim/overmind) or foreman for `bin/dev`

## Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/{{GITHUB_USER}}/{{APP_NAME}}
cd {{APP_NAME}}
bin/setup
```

The setup script installs gems, creates and migrates the database, seeds development data, and installs git pre-commit hooks.

## Start the development server

```bash
bin/dev
```

Visit [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000).

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `bin/dev` | Start development server + background job worker |
| `bin/rails test` | Run all tests |
| `bin/rails test test/models` | Model tests only |
| `bin/rails test test/controllers` | Controller tests only |
| `bin/rails test:system` | System tests (browser) |
| `bin/ci` | Full CI: rubocop + all tests |
| `make lint` | Run rubocop |
| `make lint-fix` | Auto-fix rubocop offenses |
| `bin/rails routes` | List all routes |
| `bin/rails console` | Open Rails console |
| `bin/rails db:migrate` | Run pending migrations |
| `bin/rails db:rollback` | Rollback last migration |
| `make db-reset` | Drop, recreate, migrate, seed |
| `make security` | Run brakeman static analysis |

## Using MySQL

Set `DATABASE_ADAPTER=mysql2` in your environment (or a `.env` file):

```bash
DATABASE_ADAPTER=mysql2 bin/setup
DATABASE_ADAPTER=mysql2 bin/dev
DATABASE_ADAPTER=mysql2 bin/ci
```

## Authentication in development

Magic link verification codes are logged to the Rails console â€” no email server needed:

```
[SessionMailer] Magic link code for dev@example.com: 123456
```

The seed user is `dev@example.com`. Sign in at [http://localhost:3000/session/new](http://localhost:3000/session/new).

## Architecture overview

This project follows [37signals](https://37signals.com) conventions:

| Concern | Convention |
|---------|-----------|
| Business logic | In models and concerns â€” never service objects |
| Controllers | Thin orchestrators; CRUD-only action names |
| State | Separate records (`Closure`, `Pin`) not boolean columns |
| Routes | Strict `resources`/`resource`; nominalize verbs |
| Frontend | Server-rendered ERB + Hotwire â€” not an SPA |
| CSS | Native cascade layers â€” no Tailwind |
| Jobs | Solid Queue â€” no Redis |
| Auth | Magic links â€” no Devise |
| Tests | Minitest + fixtures â€” no RSpec / FactoryBot |

See `AGENTS.md` for the complete set of conventions.

## Adding features

**New model:**
```bash
bin/rails generate model Post title:string body:text user:references
bin/rails db:migrate
```

**New CRUD resource:**
```ruby
# config/routes.rb
resources :posts

# app/controllers/posts_controller.rb
class PostsController < ApplicationController
  def index = @posts = Post.all
  def show  = @post = Post.find(params[:id])
  # ...
end
```

**State as a record (37signals pattern):**
```bash
# "close a post" â†’ Closure record, not closed_at boolean
bin/rails generate model Closure post:references user:references
```

```ruby
# config/routes.rb
resources :posts do
  scope module: :posts do
    resource :closure
  end
end
```
